OL,3,CTrain crew rescued from roaring
OL,4,Cwildfire in Canada
OL,6,FMassive plumes of wildfire smoke have
OL,7,Fstarted to pour over the border into
OL,8,Fthe US, bringing dangerous air quality
OL,9,Fto more than 100 million people in the
OL,10,FMidwest and Northeast.
OL,12,FSmoke shrouded skylines and prompted
OL,13,Fair quality alerts for several cities
OL,14,Fincluding New York, Boston, Chicago
OL,15,Fand Detroit.
OL,17,FMultiple wildfires were also burning
OL,18,Fin the US state of Minnesota, with
OL,19,Frangers working to evacuate thousands
OL,20,Fof people, including teenagers, from
OL,21,Fcamping sites in the north east.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/4
